As a Database Operations Manager, the responsibilities include:

Strategically provisioning databases and devising appropriate high availability/disaster recovery (HA/DR) solutions aligned with the business division's Recovery Time Objective (RTO) and Recovery Point Objective (RPO).
Overseeing the configuration, maintenance, and troubleshooting of critical database technologies such as log shipping, database mirroring, Always-On Availability Groups, and SQL Server Failover Cluster, ensuring seamless operation across single and multiple subnets.
Leading performance tuning initiatives, addressing complex issues spanning query optimization, index efficiency, TempDB management, IO optimization, high CPU usage, and synchronization challenges in high availability environments.
Managing the setup and configuration of SQL Server Clusters to guarantee system stability and resilience.
Orchestrating weekly patching routines for both standalone and clustered instances to uphold security and performance standards.
Spearheading migration and upgrade projects, orchestrating smooth transitions from legacy SQL Server versions to modern iterations (2016-2019).
Directing the development and support of Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, facilitating seamless data flow from diverse sources like Oracle, Sybase, Access, and Excel into SQL Server.
Ensuring the integrity of database permissions and security settings to safeguard sensitive information.
Supervising the execution of daily, weekly, monthly, and quarterly maintenance tasks, promptly resolving any encountered issues.
Driving automation initiatives through PowerShell scripting to streamline repetitive tasks and enhance operational efficiency.
Conducting comprehensive health checks on extensive server estates using scripted solutions to proactively identify and mitigate potential performance bottlenecks.
Addressing database space constraints, mitigating excessive log growth, and implementing normalization techniques to optimize database structures.
Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams to implement server, instance, and database changes in alignment with organizational objectives.
Providing dedicated support and guidance to application owners and developers, ensuring seamless database operations and performance.
